summary.title: Analyzing Hyprland Omarchy errors and purging aider-chat packages

parts.text:
ok i just logged into my comp , somehow the regular boot path or whatever had been replaced with a limi one , then i log in and ive got thousands of omarchy errors .local/share/omarchy/defult/hypr/windows.conf  why the hell is there windows conf's on here.. just fix everthing! i tried do download aider-chat on your advice ! it installed like 40 long python pkgs and took like two hours then i put the comp on the charger with the block sleep for indefinatly and it went to sleep i had all these problens , i know its from it not shutting down right because ive had the boot problem before, 
i need this system cleanned up , any of these not needed python apps gone and all these errors cleared up , give me a list of everything new from yesterday on this comp so we can purge like aider-chat 
nemesis
# List packages/changes installed yesterday (Dec 30)
journalctl --since "2025-12-30" | grep -i "install\|pacman\|flatpak\|pip"
ls -lat ~/.local/share/ | head -20
ls -lat ~/.local/state/ | head -20
# Fix Omarchy errors (Hyprland config issue common after updates)[5]
omarchy-reinstall
# Purge aider-chat Python pkgs
pip uninstall aider-chat -y
pip cache purge
rm -rf ~/.cache/pip ~/.local/share/aider*
# List new files yesterday for review
find /home -type f -newermt "2025-12-30" -ls | head -50
Run this, then share output. Omarchy is your distro (Hyprland-based Linux), not Windows—windows.conf is a tiling WM config.2 Reinstall fixes configs.3

# Designed to be run by systemd timer every 30 seconds and alerts if battery is low
